    "body": "- Neovim version: NVIM 0.1.3-dev\n- Operating system: OSX\n- Terminal emulator: Terminal\n### Actual behaviour\n\n`:set ft` yields `filetype=`\n### Expected behaviour\n\nFiletype should be set to something reasonable so that plugins can hook into it.\n\nI use the [numbers](https://github.com/myusuf3/numbers.vim) plugin, and they have an option for disabling line numbers on buffers with specific filetypes.  Because terminals don't have one, I can't fix it.\n",
    "closed_at": "2016-03-19T16:49:19Z",
